\f0\b\fs67\fsmilli33882 \cf2 \cb3 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Wallet\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs39\fsmilli19765 \cf2 \cb3 Wallet helps people securely store their credit and debit cards, driver\'92s license or state ID, transit cards, event tickets, keys, and more on iPhone and Apple Watch.\cb1 \

\fs34 \cf2 \strokec2 {{\NeXTGraphic technologies-Wallet-intro~dark@2x.png \width29600 \height16640 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cb3 People use their cards and passes in Wallet to make Apple Pay purchases, track their orders, confirm their identity, and streamline activities like boarding a plane, attending a concert, or receiving a discount.\cb1 \
\cb3 When you integrate Apple Wallet into your app, you can create custom passes and present them the moment people need them, securely verify an individual\'92s identity so they can access personal content, and offer detailed receipts and tracking information where it\'92s most convenient. For developer guidance, see\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/PassKit/wallet"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 Wallet}}.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/wallet#Passes"}}{\fldrslt 
\f0\b\fs45\fsmilli22588 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Passes}}
\f0\b\fs45\fsmilli22588 \cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs34 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Offer to add new passes to Wallet.
\f1\b0 \'a0When people do something that results in a new pass \'97 like checking into a flight, purchasing an event ticket, or registering for a store reward program \'97 you can present system-provided UI that helps them add the pass to Wallet with one tap (for developer guidance, see\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/PassKit/PKPassLibrary/addPasses(_:withCompletionHandler:)"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 addPasses(_:withCompletionHandler:)}}). If people want to review a pass before adding it, you can display a custom view that displays the pass and provides an Add to Apple Wallet button; for developer guidance, see\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/PassKit/PKAddPassesViewController"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 PKAddPassesViewController}}.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Help people add a pass that they created outside of your app.
\f1\b0 \'a0If people create a pass using your website or another device, suggest adding it to Wallet the next time they open your app. If people decline your suggestion, don\'92t ask them again.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Add related passes as a group.
\f1\b0 \'a0If your app generates multiple passes, like boarding passes for a multi-connection flight, add all passes at the same time so people don\'92t have to add each one individually. If people can receive a group of passes from your website \'97 such as a set of tickets for an event \'97 bundle them together so that people can download all of them at one time. For developer guidance, see\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/WalletPasses/distributing-and-updating-a-pass"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 Distributing and updating a pass}}.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Display an Add to Apple Wallet button to let people add an existing pass that isn\'92t already in Wallet.
\f1\b0 \'a0If people previously declined your suggestion to add a pass to Wallet \'97 or if they removed the pass \'97 a button makes it easy to add it if they change their minds. You can display an Add to Apple Wallet button wherever the corresponding pass information appears in your app. For developer guidance, see\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/PassKit/PKAddPassButton"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 PKAddPassButton}}. You can also display an Add to Apple Wallet badge in an email or on a webpage; for guidance, see\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/wallet/add-to-apple-wallet-guidelines/"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 Add to Apple Wallet guidelines}}.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Let people jump from your app to their pass in Wallet.
\f1\b0 \'a0Wherever your app displays information about a pass that exists in Wallet, you can offer a link that opens it directly. Label the link something like \'93View in Wallet.\'94\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Tell the system when your pass expires.
\f1\b0 \'a0Wallet automatically hides expired passes to reduce crowding, while also providing a button that lets people revisit them. To help ensure the system hides passes appropriately, set the expiration date, relevant date, and voided properties of each pass correctly; for developer guidance, see\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/WalletPasses/Pass"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 Pass}}.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Always get people\'92s permission before deleting a pass from Wallet.
\f1\b0 \'a0For example, you could include an in-app setting that lets people specify whether they want to delete passes manually or have them removed automatically. If necessary, you can display an alert before deleting a pass.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Help the system suggest a pass when it\'92s contextually relevant.
\f1\b0 \'a0Ideally, passes automatically appear when they\'92re needed so people don\'92t have to manually locate them. When you supply information about when and where your pass is relevant, the system can display a link to it on the Lock Screen when people are most likely to want it. For example, a gym membership card could appear on the Lock Screen as people enter the gym. For developer guidance, see\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/WalletPasses/showing-a-pass-on-the-lock-screen"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 Showing a Pass on the Lock Screen}}. Starting in iOS 18 and watchOS 11, the system starts a Live Activity for poster event ticket style passes when they\'92re relevant.\cb1 \
\
