\fs34 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 In general, a pass can have up to three header fields, one primary field, up to four secondary fields, and up to four auxiliary fields. Depending on the amount of content you display in each field, some fields may not be visible.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 Display text only in pass fields.
\f1\b0 \'a0Don\'92t embed text in images \'97 it\'92s not accessible and not all images are displayed on all devices \'97 and avoid using custom fonts that might make text hard to read.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
