\cb3 In iOS 18 and later, the system defines an additional style for contactless event tickets called\'a0
\f4\i poster event ticket
\f1\i0 . Poster event tickets offer a rich visual experience that prominently features the event artwork, provides easy access to additional event information, and integrates with system apps like Weather and Maps.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf7 \cb8 \strokec7 Important\cb1 \

\fs34 \cf2 \cb8 \strokec2 Poster event tickets aren\'92t compatible with tickets that require a QR code or barcode for entry.\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 A poster event ticket displays an event logo and background image, and can optionally display a separate ticket issuer or event company logo. The system uses metadata about your event to structure ticket information and suggest relevant actions. You must provide a required set of metadata in\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/WalletPasses/SemanticTags"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 SemanticTags}}\'a0for all poster event tickets, and an additional set of required metadata depending on the event type \'97 general, sports, or live performance. You can also add optional metadata to further enhance your ticket. For example, you can specify an admission level for a live performance, like General Admission, which the system displays with the seating information. For developer guidance, see\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/WalletPasses/supporting-semantic-tags-in-wallet-passes"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 Supporting semantic tags in Wallet passes}}.\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0
\fs19\fsmilli9882 \cf2 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/wallet#"}}{\fldrslt \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Example}}\cb1 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/wallet#"}}{\fldrslt \cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 Layout}}
