\fs34 \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 Create a vibrant and engaging background.
\f1\b0 \'a0As the centerpiece of a poster event ticket, your background image serves as a visual representation of the event. Limit text in your artwork, and create an image that\'92s easily identifiable to help people quickly find their ticket among other passes in their Wallet app. If your background image is a solid color or includes a solid color in the footer, consider setting a footer background color to better blend the background image with the footer.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Position your background image in the safe area.
\f1\b0 \'a0The system displays ticket information in the header and footer, which overlap the background image. To ensure that the content in your artwork isn\'92t covered, position it in the safe area. For developer guidance, see\'a0
\f3 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 footerBackgroundColor
\f1 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0in\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/WalletPasses/Pass"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 Pass}}.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Ensure sufficient contrast so that ticket information is easy to read.
\f1\b0 \'a0By default, the system applies a gradient in the header and a blur effect in the footer of your poster event ticket to provide sufficient contrast between the background image and ticket information. Consider adjusting the gradient and blur effect if you need more contrast. The system can also automatically determine the best text color for ticket information and labels based on your background image. If you choose to customize text colors, make sure to select a color that provides sufficient contrast, especially if you set a footer background color or a seat section color to support wayfinding. For developer guidance, see\'a0
\f3 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 useAutomaticColors
\f1 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0in\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/WalletPasses/Pass"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 Pass}}\'a0and\'a0
\f3 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 seatSectionColor
\f1 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0in\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/WalletPasses/SemanticTagType/Seat-data.dictionary"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 SemanticTagType.Seat}}.\cb1 \
