\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 Consider using the additional information tile for extra event details.
\f1\b0 \'a0When you have more information about the event that people may find helpful, the additional information tile below the ticket is a great place to put it. If you have additional information that\'92s essential to display on the front of the ticket, keep the text short to avoid cluttering the footer. For developer guidance, see\'a0
\f3 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 additionalTicketAttributes
\f1 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0in\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/WalletPasses/SemanticTags"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 SemanticTags}}\'a0and\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/WalletPasses/PassFields/AdditionalInfoFields-data.dictionary"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 PassFields.AdditionalInfoFields}}.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Continue to support event tickets for earlier versions of iOS.
\f1\b0 \'a0People expect contactless event tickets to work, regardless of their device\'92s software version. Continue to provide primary, secondary, and auxiliary information in\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/WalletPasses/PassFields"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 PassFields}}\'a0and image assets for your event ticket. This enables the system to automatically generate the appropriate ticket style for a person\'92s device; otherwise, your ticket appears empty on devices running earlier versions of iOS.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/wallet#Generic-passes"}}{\fldrslt 
\fs33\fsmilli16941 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Generic passes}}
\fs33\fsmilli16941 \cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs34 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Use the generic style for a type of pass that doesn\'92t fit into the other categories, such as a gym membership card or coat-check claim ticket. A generic pass can display logo and thumbnail images, and it can have up to four secondary and auxiliary fields, all displayed on one row.\cb1 \
