\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Wallet presents a dashboard that displays a customer\'92s active and completed orders. People can choose an order to view details about it, like the items they ordered and fulfillment information for shipping and pickup.\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 {{\NeXTGraphic Attachment.png \width320 \height320 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0

\fs19\fsmilli9882 \cf2 \cb3 Dashboard\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa340\partightenfactor0

\fs34 \cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 The\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/WalletOrders"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 Wallet Orders}}\'a0schema defines the properties you use to provide order data like product descriptions, order status, contact information, and shipping and pickup details, including estimated arrival dates, addresses, tracking numbers, and pickup instructions. Wallet displays the information you supply within consistent, system-defined interfaces. To help people get the information they need quickly and conveniently, supply as much information as you can, using the properties that match your order processes.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 {{\NeXTGraphic Attachment.png \width320 \height320 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 Make it easy for people to add an order to Wallet.
\f1\b0 \'a0For example, when a customer completes an Apple Pay transaction in your app or website, use\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/PassKit/PKPaymentOrderDetails"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 PKPaymentOrderDetails}}\'a0(app) or\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/ApplePayontheWeb/ApplePayPaymentOrderDetails"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 ApplePayPaymentOrderDetails}}\'a0(web) to automatically add the order to Wallet. In iOS 17 and later, you can use\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/FinanceKitUI/AddOrderToWalletButton"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 AddOrderToWalletButton}}\'a0to display the system-provided Track with Apple Wallet button in relevant areas of your app or website \'97 such as in pages for order confirmation, status, or tracking \'97 or in emails to customers. If a person already added an order to Wallet, trying to add it again opens Wallet and displays the order.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Make information about an order available immediately after people place it.
\f1\b0 \'a0People need to confirm that their order was received, even when payment, processing, and fulfillment are still pending. If you won\'92t have details until a later time, provide the data you have at the time of the order and supply a status\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/walletorders/order"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 description}}\'a0like \'93Check back later for full order details.\'94\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Provide fulfillment information as soon as it\'92s available, and keep the status up to date.
\f1\b0 \'a0When you supply fulfillment data or you change the status of an order, the system updates the order information and can automatically send a notification to customers. The system uses the fulfillment status you report to update the order\'92s current status to a value like Order Placed, Processing, Ready for Pickup, Picked Up, Out for Delivery, Delivered, or \'97 if something goes wrong \'97 Issue or Canceled. For guidance on describing a status, see\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/wallet#Displaying-order-and-fulfillment-details"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 Displaying order and fulfillment details}}.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Supply a high-resolution logo image that uses a nontransparent background.
\f1\b0 \'a0The system displays your logo image in the dashboard and detail view, so you want to make sure that people can instantly recognize it at various sizes. Use the PNG or JPEG format to create a logo image that measures 300x300 pixels. To help ensure that your logo image renders correctly, be sure to use a nontransparent background. For developer guidance, see\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/walletorders/merchant"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 logo}}.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Supply distinct, high-resolution product images that use nontransparent backgrounds.
\f1\b0 \'a0The system displays a product\'92s image \'97 along with descriptive information you supply \'97 in the detail views, order dashboard, and notifications for an order or a fulfillment. When creating a product image, use a straightforward depiction and a solid, nontransparent background. Showing a product in a \'93lifestyle\'94 context or against a busy background can make the item hard to distinguish at small sizes. For each product, use the PNG or JPEG format to create an image that measures 300x300 pixels.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 {{\NeXTGraphic Attachment.png \width320 \height320 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 In general, keep text brief.
\f1\b0 \'a0People appreciate being able to read text at a glance, and the system can truncate text that\'92s too long.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Use clear, approachable language, and localize the text you provide.
\f1\b0 \'a0You want to make sure that all your customers can read the information in an order. Also, make sure the price you show matches the final price the customer confirmed.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/wallet#Displaying-order-and-fulfillment-details"}}{\fldrslt 
\fs39\fsmilli19765 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Displaying order and fulfillment details}}
\fs39\fsmilli19765 \cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs34 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 An order gives people ways to contact the merchant and displays details about their Apple Pay purchase, including fulfillment status and per-item information.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 Provide a link to an area where people manage their order.
\f1\b0 \'a0When you provide a universal link, people can open your order management area even if they don\'92t have your app installed. To learn more about universal links, see\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/Xcode/allowing-apps-and-websites-to-link-to-your-content"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 Allowing apps and websites to link to your content}}; for developer guidance, see\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/WalletOrders/Order"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 Order}}.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Clearly describe each item so people can verify that their order contains everything they expect.
\f1\b0 \'a0You can use the\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/WalletOrders/LineItem"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 LineItem}}\'a0property to provide information like a product\'92s price, name, and image. An order lists the line items for every item the customer ordered; a fulfillment lists only the line items that fulfillment includes. When appropriate, you can also attach a PDF receipt to an individual transaction related to an order.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Supply a prioritized list of your apps that might be installed on the device.
\f1\b0 \'a0The system uses this list when it needs to display a link to your app within the order details view. For example, if you provide multiple apps and more than one of them is installed on the device, the system displays a link to the installed app that\'92s highest on your list. If none of your apps are installed on the device, the system displays a link to the first app on your list. For developer guidance, see\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/WalletOrders/Order"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 Order}}.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Avoid sending duplicate notifications.
\f1\b0 \'a0For example, you can tell the system to avoid sending order-related notifications through Wallet when the customer has one of your associated apps installed.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Make it easy for customers to contact the merchant.
\f1\b0 \'a0Provide multiple contact methods, so people can choose the one that works best for them. At minimum, you need to provide a link to the merchant\'92s website or landing page, but you can also provide a Messages for Business link, a phone number, an email address, and a link to a support page. When people choose the Contact button in an order, the system displays a menu of the contact methods you supply. For developer guidance, see\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/WalletOrders/Merchant"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 Merchant}}.\cb1 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 {{\NeXTGraphic Attachment.png \width320 \height320 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa340\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 Help people track their order.
\f1\b0 \'a0A multi-item order can have multiple fulfillments, where each fulfillment is either shipping or pickup. For example, if a customer orders a pair of shoes and a T-shirt, the customer might want to have one item shipped, while picking up the other. Regardless of fulfillment type, you need to supply enough information for people to know where their items are and when to expect them at the destination they specified. In addition to an estimated time of arrival, here\'92s some information that people particularly appreciate:\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls8\ilvl0\cf2 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 A link that opens the carrier\'92s website to a page with information about a shipping fulfillment. When possible, provide a direct link \'97 in addition to a tracking number \'97 so people can easily view the most up-to-date shipping information. If necessary, display this link on any intermediate order-tracking page you open.\cb1 \
\ls8\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 A scannable barcode when one is required to pick up the order in a pickup fulfillment. It\'92s convenient when people can offer the barcode from within Wallet instead of finding it in an email or webpage.\cb1 \
\ls8\ilvl0\cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Clear, detailed instructions that can help people receive or pick up their order.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 {{\NeXTGraphic Attachment.png \width320 \height320 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa340\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 Keep the fulfillment screen centered on order tracking.
\f1\b0 \'a0For example, if you recommend your app or other services to customers, be sure to prioritize order-tracking information over other content in the screen.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Choose shipping-fulfillment values that match the details you have about the shipping process.
\f1\b0 \'a0If you know the carrier, enter its name in the\'a0
\f3 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 carrier
\f1 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0property; otherwise, leave the default \'93Track Shipment\'94 value. If you can access details about a carrier\'92s interim shipping steps \'97 such as when a fulfillment is on the way or out for delivery \'97 indicate each step by using specific status values like\'a0
\f3 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 onTheWay
\f1 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 ,\'a0
\f3 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 outForDelivery
\f1 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 , or\'a0
\f3 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 delivered
\f1 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 . In contrast, if you don\'92t have access to a carrier\'92s shipping details, use the\'a0
\f3 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 shipped
\f1 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 \'a0status. In both cases, provide a tracking link (when one is available) so people can track their order on their own. For developer guidance, see\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/WalletOrders/ShippingFulfillment"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 ShippingFulfillment}}.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Keep customers informed through relevant fulfillment status descriptions.
\f1\b0 \'a0A great status message is approachable, accurate, and clearly related to the status it describes. In addition to supplying information that helps people understand the status of their order, a status message also gives you an opportunity to use your brand\'92s communication style.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Be direct and thorough when describing an Issue or Canceled status.
\f1\b0 \'a0People generally need to know why there\'92s a problem and what they can do about it.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/wallet#Identity-verification"}}{\fldrslt 
\f0\b\fs45\fsmilli22588 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Identity verification}}
\f0\b\fs45\fsmilli22588 \cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs34 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 On iPhone running iOS 16 and later, people can store an ID card in Wallet, and later allow an app or App Clip to access information on the card to verify their identity without leaving their current context. For example, a person might need to confirm their identity when they apply for a credit card within their banking app. To learn how to support in-person mobile ID verification, see\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/id-verifier"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 ID Verifier}}.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf9 \cb10 \strokec9 Developer note\cb1 \

\fs34 \cf2 \cb10 \strokec2 Apple doesn\'92t create or see the ID documents that people add to Wallet, and when people agree to share identifying information with your app, you receive only encrypted data that isn\'92t readable on the device. For developer guidance, see\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/PassKit/requesting-identity-data-from-a-wallet-pass"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb10 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 Requesting identity data from a Wallet pass}}.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 To help you offer a consistent experience that people can trust, Apple provides a Verify with Wallet button you can use in your app when you need to ask for identify verification. The button reveals a sheet that describes your request and lets people agree to share their information or cancel.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 Present a Wallet verification option only when the device supports it.
\f1\b0 \'a0If the current device can\'92t return the identify information you request, don\'92t display a Verify with Apple Wallet button. Be prepared to present a fallback view that offers a different verification method if Verify with Apple Wallet isn\'92t available; for developer guidance, see\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/PassKit/VerifyIdentityWithWalletButton"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 VerifyIdentityWithWalletButton}}.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Ask for identity information only at the precise moment you need it.
\f1\b0 \'a0People can be suspicious of a request for personal information if it doesn\'92t seem to be related to their current action. If your app needs identity verification, for example, wait to ask for this information until people are completing the process or transaction that requires it; don\'92t request verification before people are ready to start the process or when they\'92re simply creating an account.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Clearly and succinctly describe the reason you need the information you\'92re requesting.
\f1\b0 \'a0You must write text that explains why people need to share identity information with your app (this text is called a\'a0
\f4\i purpose string
\f1\i0 \'a0or\'a0
\f4\i usage description string
\f1\i0 ). The system displays your purpose string in the verification sheet so people can make an informed decision. Here are a couple of examples:\cb1 \

