\fs34 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 For each purpose string, aim for a brief, complete sentence that\'92s direct, specific, and easy for everyone to understand. Use sentence case, avoid passive voice, and include a period at the end.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 Ask only for the data you actually need.
\f1\b0 \'a0People may lose trust in your app if you ask for more data than you need to complete the current task or action. For example, if you need to ensure that a customer is at least a certain age, use a request that specifies an age threshold; avoid requesting the customer\'92s current age or birth date. For developer guidance, see\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/PassKit/PKIdentityElement/age(atLeast:)"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 age(atLeast:)}}.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Clearly indicate whether you will keep the data and \'97 if you need to keep it \'97 specify how long you\'92ll do so.
\f1\b0 \'a0To help people trust your app, it\'92s essential to explain how long you might need to keep the personal information they agree to share with you. When you use PassKit APIs to specify a duration \'97 such as a particular period, indefinitely, or only as long as it takes to complete the current verification \'97 the system automatically displays explanatory content in the verification sheet. For developer guidance, see\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/PassKit/PKIdentityIntentToStore"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 PKIdentityIntentToStore}}.\cb1 \

