\fs34 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf11 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/design/resources/#macos-apps"}}{\fldrslt \cf12 \ul \ulc12 Apple Design Resources}} provides a template you can use to create a custom background fill and center image for a document icon. As you use this template, follow the guidelines below.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf11 Design simple images that clearly communicate the document type.
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539  Whether you use a background fill, a center image, or both, prefer uncomplicated shapes and a reduced palette of distinct colors. Your document icon can display as small as 16x16 px, so you want to create designs that remain recognizable at every size.\

\f0\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 Designing a single, expressive image for the background fill can be a great way to help people understand and recognize a document type.
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539  For example, Xcode and TextEdit both use rich background images that don\'92t include a center image.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf11 {{\NeXTGraphic doc-icon-custom-1@2x.png \width6400 \height6400 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf11 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf11 {{\NeXTGraphic doc-icon-fill-only@2x.png \width6400 \height6400 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf11 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf11 Consider reducing complexity in the small versions of your document icon.
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539  Icon details that are clear in large versions can look blurry and be hard to recognize in small versions. For example, to ensure that the grid lines in the custom heart document icon remain clear in intermediate sizes, you might use fewer lines and thicken them by aligning them to the reduced pixel grid. In the 16x16 px size, you might remove the lines altogether.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf11 {{\NeXTGraphic doc-icon-fewer-details-1@2x.png \width6400 \height6400 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf11 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf11 The 32x32 px icon has fewer grid lines and a thicker EKG line.\
