\f0\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf11 Specify a succinct term if it helps people understand your document type.
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539  By default, the system displays a document\'92s extension at the bottom edge of the document icon, but if the extension is unfamiliar you can supply a more descriptive term. For example, the document icon for a SceneKit scene file uses the term 
\f4\i \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 scene
\f1\i0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539  instead of the file extension 
\f4\i \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 scn
\f1\i0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 . The system automatically scales the extension text to fit in the document icon, so be sure to use a term that\'92s short enough to be legible at small sizes. By default, the system capitalizes every letter in the text\
