\f0\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf13 \cb14 Developer note\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf11 \cb14 You can use the constants defined in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/SwiftUI/Font/Design"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \AppleTypeServices \cf12 \cb14 \ul \ulc12 Font.Design}} to access all system fonts \'97 don\'92t embed system fonts in your app or game. For example, use {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/SwiftUI/Font/Design/default"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \AppleTypeServices \cf12 \cb14 \ul \ulc12 Font.Design.default}} to get the system font on all platforms; use {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/SwiftUI/Font/Design/serif"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \AppleTypeServices \cf12 \cb14 \ul \ulc12 Font.Design.serif}} to get the New York font.\cf11 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf11 If necessary, adjust tracking in interface mockups.
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539  In a running app, the system font dynamically adjusts tracking at every point size. To produce an accurate interface mockup of an interface that uses the variable system fonts, you don\'92t have to choose a discrete optical size at certain point sizes, but you might need to adjust the tracking. For guidance, see {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/typography#Tracking-values"}}{\fldrslt \cf12 \ul \ulc12 Tracking values}}.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/typography#Using-custom-fonts"}}{\fldrslt 
\f0\b\fs56 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf11 Using custom fonts}}
\f0\b\fs56 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs34 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf11 Make sure custom fonts are legible.
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539  People need to be able to read your custom font easily at various viewing distances and under a variety of conditions. While using a custom font, be guided by the recommended minimum font sizes for various styles and weights in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/typography#Specifications"}}{\fldrslt \cf12 \ul \ulc12 Specifications}}.\

\f0\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 Implement accessibility features for custom fonts.
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539  System fonts automatically support Dynamic Type (where available) and respond when people turn on accessibility features, such as Bold Text. If you use a custom font, make sure it implements the same behaviors. For developer guidance, see {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/SwiftUI/Applying-Custom-Fonts-to-Text"}}{\fldrslt \cf12 \ul \ulc12 Applying custom fonts to text}}. In a Unity-based game, you can use {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://github.com/apple/unityplugins"}}{\fldrslt \cf12 \ul \ulc12 Apple\'92s Unity plug-ins}} to support Dynamic Type. If the plug-in isn\'92t appropriate for your game, be sure to let players adjust text size in other ways.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/typography#Supporting-Dynamic-Type"}}{\fldrslt 
\f0\b\fs56 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf11 Supporting Dynamic Type}}
\f0\b\fs56 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs34 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf11 Dynamic Type is a system-level feature in iOS, iPadOS, tvOS, visionOS, and watchOS that lets people adjust the size of visible text on their device to ensure readability and comfort. For related guidance, see {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/accessibility"}}{\fldrslt \cf12 \ul \ulc12 Accessibility}}.\
