The 
\f4\i \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 clear
\f1\i0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539  variant is highly translucent, which is ideal for prioritizing the visibility of the underlying content and ensuring visually rich background elements remain prominent. Use this variant for components that float above media backgrounds \'97 such as photos and videos \'97 to create a more immersive content experience.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf11 {{\NeXTGraphic materials-ios-liquid-glass-clear@2x.png \width9320 \height9320 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf11 \
For optimal contrast and legibility, determine whether to add a dimming layer behind components with clear Liquid Glass:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls12\ilvl0\cf11 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
If the underlying content is bright, consider adding a dark dimming layer of 35% opacity. For developer guidance, see {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/SwiftUI/Glass/clear"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \AppleTypeServices \cf12 \ul \ulc12 clear}}.\
\ls12\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
If the underlying content is sufficiently dark, or if you use standard media playback controls from AVKit that provide their own dimming layer, you don\'92t need to apply a dimming layer.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf11 For guidance about the use of color, see {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/color#Liquid-Glass-color"}}{\fldrslt \cf12 \ul \ulc12 Liquid Glass color}}.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/materials#Standard-materials"}}{\fldrslt 
\f0\b\fs56 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf11 Standard materials}}
\f0\b\fs56 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs34 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf11 Use standard materials and effects \'97 such as {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/UIKit/UIBlurEffect"}}{\fldrslt \cf12 \ul \ulc12 blur}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/UIKit/UIVibrancyEffect"}}{\fldrslt \cf12 \ul \ulc12 vibrancy}}, and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/AppKit/NSVisualEffectView/BlendingMode-swift.enum"}}{\fldrslt \cf12 \ul \ulc12 blending modes}} \'97 to convey a sense of structure in the content beneath Liquid Glass.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 \cf11 Choose materials and effects based on semantic meaning and recommended usage.
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539  Avoid selecting a material or effect based on the apparent color it imparts to your interface, because system settings can change its appearance and behavior. Instead, match the material or vibrancy style to your specific use case.\

\f0\b \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539 Help ensure legibility by using vibrant colors on top of materials.
\f1\b0 \AppleTypeServices\AppleTypeServicesF65539  When you use system-defined vibrant colors, you don\'92t need to worry about colors seeming too dark, bright, saturated, or low contrast in different contexts. Regardless of the material you choose, use vibrant colors on top of it. For guidance, see {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/color#System-colors"}}{\fldrslt \cf12 \ul \ulc12 System colors}}.\
