\f0\b\fs67\fsmilli33882 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Lockups\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs39\fsmilli19765 \cf2 \cb3 Lockups combine multiple separate views into a single, interactive unit.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs34 \cf2 {{\NeXTGraphic Attachment.png \width320 \height320 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Each lockup consists of a content view, a header, and a footer. Headers appear above the main content for a lockup, and footers appear below the main content. All three views expand and contract together as the lockup gets focus.\cb1 \
\cb3 According to the needs of your app, you can combine four types of lockup: cards, caption buttons, monograms, and posters.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/lockups#Best-practices"}}{\fldrslt 
\f0\b\fs45\fsmilli22588 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Best practices}}
\f0\b\fs45\fsmilli22588 \cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs34 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Allow adequate space between lockups.
\f1\b0 \'a0A focused lockup expands in size, so leave enough room between lockups to avoid overlapping or displacing other lockups. For guidance, see\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/layout"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 Layout}}.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 {{\NeXTGraphic Attachment.png \width320 \height320 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 Use consistent lockup sizes within a row or group.
\f1\b0 \'a0A group of buttons or a row of content images is more visually appealing when the widths and heights of all elements match.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 For developer guidance, see\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/TVUIKit/TVLockupView"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 TVLockupView}}\'a0and\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/TVUIKit/TVLockupHeaderFooterView"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 TVLockupHeaderFooterView}}.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/lockups#Cards"}}{\fldrslt 
\f0\b\fs45\fsmilli22588 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Cards}}
\f0\b\fs45\fsmilli22588 \cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs34 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 A card combines a header, footer, and content view to present ratings and reviews for media items.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 {{\NeXTGraphic Attachment.png \width320 \height320 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 For developer guidance, see\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/TVUIKit/TVCardView"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 TVCardView}}.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/lockups#Caption-buttons"}}{\fldrslt 
\f0\b\fs45\fsmilli22588 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Caption buttons}}
\f0\b\fs45\fsmilli22588 \cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs34 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 A caption button can include a title and a subtitle beneath the button. A caption button can contain either an image or text.\cb1 \
\cb3 Make sure that when people focus on them, caption buttons tilt with the motion that they swipe. When aligned vertically, caption buttons tilt up and down. When aligned horizontally, caption buttons tilt left and right. When displayed in a grid, caption buttons tilt both vertically and horizontally.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 {{\NeXTGraphic Attachment.png \width320 \height320 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 For developer guidance, see\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/TVUIKit/TVCaptionButtonView"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 TVCaptionButtonView}}.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/lockups#Monograms"}}{\fldrslt 
\f0\b\fs45\fsmilli22588 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Monograms}}
\f0\b\fs45\fsmilli22588 \cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs34 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Monograms identify people, usually the cast and crew for a media item. Each monogram consists of a circular picture of the person and their name. If an image isn\'92t available, the person\'92s initials appear in place of an image.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b \cf2 \cb3 Prefer images over initials.
\f1\b0 \'a0An image of a person creates a more intimate connection than text.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 {{\NeXTGraphic Attachment.png \width320 \height320 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 For developer guidance, see\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/TVUIKit/TVMonogramContentView"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 TVMonogramContentView}}.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/lockups#Posters"}}{\fldrslt 
\f0\b\fs45\fsmilli22588 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Posters}}
\f0\b\fs45\fsmilli22588 \cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs34 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Posters consist of an image and an optional title and subtitle, which are hidden until the poster comes into focus. Posters can be any size, but the size needs to be appropriate for their content. For related guidance, see\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/image-views"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 Image views}}.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 {{\NeXTGraphic Attachment.png \width320 \height320 \appleattachmentpadding0 \appleembedtype0 \appleaqc
}¬}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \strokec2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 For developer guidance, see\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/documentation/TVUIKit/TVPosterView"}}{\fldrslt 
\f3 \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 TVPosterView}}.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/lockups#Platform-considerations"}}{\fldrslt 
\f0\b\fs45\fsmilli22588 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Platform considerations}}
\f0\b\fs45\fsmilli22588 \cf2 \strokec2 \
