\f2\fs34 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Provide actions that support the main tasks people perform.
\f1\b0 \'a0In general, prioritize the commands that people are most likely to want. These commands are often the ones people use most frequently, but in some apps it might make sense to prioritize commands that map to the highest level or most important objects people work with.\cb1 \

\f2\b \cb3 Make sure the meaning of each control is clear.
\f1\b0 \'a0Don\'92t make people guess or experiment to figure out what a toolbar item does. Prefer simple, recognizable symbols for items instead of text, except for actions like\'a0
\f4\i edit
\f1\i0 \'a0that aren\'92t well-represented by symbols. For guidance on symbols that represent common actions, see\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://developer.apple.com/design/human-interface-guidelines/icons#Standard-icons"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb3 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 Standard icons}}.\cb1 \
